        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "There is a mistake in *Zend\/Controller\/Router\/Route\/Regex.php*, function __getMappedValues()_.\nWhen __getMappedValues()_ is used by _assemble()_ (parameter *$reversed* == _true_), it makes wrong array of values.\nBy documentation, Map array can be written in any direction of mapped values ( _1_ => _'name'_ or _'name'_ => _1_).\nSo, when url is assembled, this code is executed:\n\n{code}\n...\n} elseif ($reversed) {\n    $index = (!is_int($key)) ? array_search($key, $this->_map, true) : $key;\n    if (false !== $index) {\n        $return[$index] = $values[$key];\n    }\n} elseif ($preserve) {\n....\n{code}\n\nIn case when *$key* == _'name'_ and *$_map* == _array('name' => 1)_, _array_search(...)_ will return false and value will not be mapped.\nMy patch is:\n\n{noformat}\n--- sources\/framework\/library\/Zend\/Controller\/Router\/Route\/Regex.php\t(revision 106)\n+++ sources\/framework\/library\/Zend\/Controller\/Router\/Route\/Regex.php\t(revision 107)\n@@ -136,7 +136,15 @@\n                 }\n                 $return[$index] = $values[$key];\n             } elseif ($reversed) {\n-                $index = (!is_int($key)) ? array_search($key, $this->_map, true) : $key;\n+                if (!is_int($key)) {\n+                    if (array_key_exists($key, $this->_map)) {\n+                        $index = $this->_map[$key];\n+                    } else {\n+                        $index = array_search($key, $this->_map, true);\n+                    }\n+                } else {\n+                    $index = $key;\n+                }\n                 if (false !== $index) {\n                     $return[$index] = $values[$key];\n                 }\n{noformat}"
        },
